OL,3,CJuly 4 General Election: How do you
OL,4,Cregister to vote and do you need ID?
OL,6,FYou can opt to vote by post if you're
OL,7,Faway from home or you're abroad and
OL,8,Fwanting to vote in England, Scotland
OL,9,Fand Wales.
OL,11,FIf you're unable to vote in person you
OL,12,Fcan ask someone to vote on your
OL,13,Fbehalf. This is called a proxy vote.
OL,15,FYou can only apply for a proxy vote
OL,16,Funder certain circumstances,
OL,17,Fincluding: being away on polling day,
OL,18,Fbeing registered as an overseas voter,
OL,19,Fhaving a medical issue or disability,
OL,20,Fand not being able to vote in person
OL,21,Fbecause of work or military service.
