OL,3,CJuly 4 General Election: How do you
OL,4,Cregister to vote and do you need ID?
OL,6,FYour proxy should be someone you trust
OL,7,Fto vote on your behalf. You'll need to
OL,8,Ftell them which candidate you want to
OL,9,Fvote for.
OL,11,FHave you heard our new podcast Talking
OL,12,FPolitics? Every week Tom, Robert and
OL,13,FAnushka dig into the biggest issues
OL,14,Fdominating the political agenda...
OL,16,FWhat sort of ID is accepted?
OL,18,FFor the first time in a General
OL,19,FElection, everyone must show photo ID
OL,20,Fwhen voting in person in England,
OL,21,FScotland and Wales.
